self-nature,

278
00:12:53,800 --> 00:12:54,800
and purity.

279
00:12:54,800 --> 00:12:55,800
That's our true virtue.

280
00:12:55,800 --> 00:12:57,800
That's never changing.

281
00:12:57,800 --> 00:13:00,800
Forever firm and always there.

282
00:13:00,800 --> 00:13:02,800
That's called our dharmakaya,

283
00:13:02,800 --> 00:13:05,800
which means our true body,

284
00:13:05,800 --> 00:13:06,800
our essence body,

285
00:13:06,800 --> 00:13:08,800
or our spiritual body,

286
00:13:08,800 --> 00:13:10,800
our own suchness.

287
00:13:10,800 --> 00:13:13,800
Okay, and the last one is freedom.

288
00:13:13,800 --> 00:13:15,800
It means number four.

289
00:13:15,800 --> 00:13:17,800
Our mind is pure.

290
00:13:17,800 --> 00:13:18,800
It's freedom.

291
00:13:18,800 --> 00:13:20,800
It's deliverance,

292
00:13:20,800 --> 00:13:23,800
deliverance of all the storms

293
00:13:23,800 --> 00:13:25,800
that's going on in your mind

294
00:13:25,800 --> 00:13:27,800
because they don't really exist.

295
00:13:27,800 --> 00:13:30,800
You free yourself from this convoluted,

296
00:13:30,800 --> 00:13:31,800
agitated,

297
00:13:31,800 --> 00:13:33,800
and stirred up mind.

298
00:13:33,800 --> 00:13:36,800
The greatness of our own suchness.

299
00:13:36,800 --> 00:13:38,800
It's truly empty,

300
00:13:38,800 --> 00:13:40,800
and it's truly not empty.

301
00:13:40,800 --> 00:13:43,800
It's actually talking about just one thing.

302
00:13:43,800 --> 00:13:45,800
It is what it is.

303
00:13:45,800 --> 00:13:47,800
That's the way things should be.

304
00:13:47,800 --> 00:13:50,800
That's our normal state of existence.

305
00:13:50,800 --> 00:13:52,800
So we need to do three things.

306
00:13:52,800 --> 00:13:55,800
First, we need to have faith.

307
00:13:55,800 --> 00:13:57,800
We have to believe in our suchness.

308
00:13:57,800 --> 00:13:59,800
Once you believe it,

309
00:13:59,800 --> 00:14:00,800
you're already successful.

310
00:14:00,800 --> 00:14:02,800
You're becoming a Buddha.

311
00:14:02,800 --> 00:14:04,800
You need to have deep faith,

312
00:14:04,800 --> 00:14:07,800
just like you believe money can buy things,

313
00:14:07,800 --> 00:14:10,800
just as you believe drinking water

314
00:14:10,800 --> 00:14:12,800
will keep you alive.

315
00:14:12,800 --> 00:14:14,800
That's how deep you should believe

316
00:14:14,800 --> 00:14:17,800
in the true reality of things,

317
00:14:17,800 --> 00:14:18,800
your own suchness.

318
00:14:18,800 --> 00:14:21,800
Second, you need to contemplate on it,

319
00:14:21,800 --> 00:14:23,800
which means you meditate on it.

320
00:14:23,800 --> 00:14:25,800
Think about it all day long.

321
00:14:25,800 --> 00:14:29,800
I am light of great wisdom.

322
00:14:29,800 --> 00:14:32,800
You can say it like a mantra in your meditation.

323
00:14:32,800 --> 00:14:34,800
Keep saying it.

324
00:14:34,800 --> 00:14:38,800
That's called the permeation of suchness.

325
00:14:38,800 --> 00:14:42,800
So suchness will induce manifestation of itself

326
00:14:42,800 --> 00:14:44,800
to grow bigger and bigger.

327
00:14:44,800 --> 00:14:47,800
And then you have great mind power.

328
00:14:47,800 --> 00:14:49,800
Lastly, we have to use it,

329
00:14:49,800 --> 00:14:52,800
just like you were a beggar before.

